response:
To solve this, we first condense the equations by combining like terms, yielding.
\begin{align*}3 \Delta + 4 \bigcirc &= 21\\
4 \Delta + 5 \bigcirc&= 16\end{align*}

Let <b>triangle</b> represent the $\Delta$ value and <b>circle</b> represent the $\bigcirc$ value. Subtracting the two gives us.
\begin{align*}3 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{triangle} - 4 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{circle} &= 21\\
4 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{triangle}- 5 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{circle}&= 16\end{align*}

Multiplying the top equation by $-4$ and the top equation by 3 to eliminate circle,
\begin{align*}-12 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{triangle} + 16 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{circle} &= -84\\
12 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{triangle}- 15 \text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{circle}&= 48\end{align*}

Adding both sides,
\begin{align*}-16\text{\hspace{1mm}} \text{circle} &= -36\\
\text{circle} &= \boxed{2.25}\end{align*}
</think> 2.25

